## AI Workflow

This project includes the persistent planner/implementer/reviewer/tester workflow with file-based coordination, plus the PO orchestration layer.
Manual and auto are two runtime modes for the same scaffold: they use the same generated files, task board, review gates, and test gates.

### Runtime modes

- Manual mode: start the planner, implementer, reviewer, and tester in separate terminals, then drive each session yourself with the documented text commands.
- Auto mode: run `scripts/ai-po.sh` to start the PO session, which uses MCP tools to coordinate the same planner, implementer, reviewer, and tester workflow for you.

### Concepts

**Cycle** — a unit of work on a feature branch. One cycle = one branch = one PR.

**Roles and file ownership:**

| Role | Reads | Writes |
|------|-------|--------|
| PO | `.ai/TASKS.md`, `.ai/PLAN.md`, `.ai/REVIEW.md`, `.ai/TEST_REPORT.md`, `.ai/prompts/po.md` | MCP session commands via `scripts/ai-po.sh` |
| Planner | `ROADMAP.md` | `.ai/PLAN.md`, `.ai/TASKS.md` |
| Implementer | `.ai/PLAN.md`, `.ai/REVIEW.md` | source code, `.ai/TASKS.md` |
| Reviewer | `.ai/PLAN.md`, commits | `.ai/REVIEW.md`, `.ai/TASKS.md` |
| Tester | `.ai/PLAN.md`, commits | `.ai/TEST_REPORT.md`, `.ai/TASKS.md` |

**Status flow:**

```
in_planning → ready_for_implement → in_implementation → ready_for_review → in_review → ready_for_test → in_testing → done
                                          ↑                                     |                              |
                                          └──── changes_requested ◄─────────────┘                              |
                                                ▲                                                               |
                                                └──────────────────────────── test_failed ◄──────────────────────┘
```

### Start a new development cycle

```bash
# Edit ROADMAP.md with your goals first, then:
scripts/ai-start-cycle.sh feature/<scope>
```

### Start persistent role sessions (manual mode)

```bash
scripts/ai-plan.sh          # terminal 1
scripts/ai-implement.sh     # terminal 2
scripts/ai-review.sh        # terminal 3
scripts/ai-test.sh          # terminal 4
```

Launch each role once, then keep those sessions open for the rest of the cycle.

### Start the PO orchestrator (auto mode)

```bash
scripts/ai-po.sh
```

The PO session drives the same task board and role flow through the `agentinit` MCP server.

### Drive work inside the existing sessions

```text
planner> start_plan
implementer> next_task T-001
reviewer> next_task T-001
tester> next_task T-001
implementer> rework_task T-001
reviewer> finish_cycle
```

**Planner commands:**

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `start_plan` | Read `ROADMAP.md`, write `.ai/PLAN.md` and `.ai/TASKS.md` |
| `rework_plan [TASK_ID]` | Revisit the plan when scope or approach changes |

**Implementer commands:**

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `next_task [TASK_ID]` | Pick up the next `ready_for_implement` task |
| `rework_task [TASK_ID]` | Address `changes_requested` or `test_failed` findings |
| `status_cycle [TASK_ID]` | Show task status and recommended next action |

**Reviewer commands:**

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `next_task [TASK_ID]` | Pick up the next `ready_for_review` task |
| `status_cycle [TASK_ID]` | Show task status and recommended next action |
| `finish_cycle [TASK_ID]` | Close the cycle after all tasks reach `done` |

**Tester commands:**

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `next_task [TASK_ID]` | Pick up the next `ready_for_test` task |
| `status_cycle [TASK_ID]` | Show task status and recommended next action |

### File map

| File | Purpose | Tracked |
|------|---------|---------|
| `.ai/PLAN.md` | Current plan | yes |
| `.ai/TASKS.md` | Task board with status | yes |
| `.ai/AGENTS.md` | Workflow-managed agent rules and session model | yes |
| `.ai/prompts/po.md` | PO orchestration prompt for auto mode | yes |
| `.ai/REVIEW.md` | Review findings | no (gitignored runtime artifact) |
| `.ai/TEST_REPORT.md` | Test findings | no (gitignored runtime artifact) |
| `.ai/HANDOFF.md` | Runtime handoff log | no |
| `ROADMAP.md` | Cycle goals (edit before planning) | yes |
| `AGENTS.md` | Project-specific agent rules and validation | yes |
| `CLAUDE.md` | Agent instruction entry point (`@AGENTS.md`) | yes |
| `scripts/ai-po.sh` | Launch the PO orchestration session | yes |

### Create a PR

```bash
scripts/ai-pr.sh sync
```

Full workflow details and session recovery rules are in `.ai/AGENTS.md`.
